---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy | PepTalk Peptides" description="Privacy policy for PepTalk Peptides — how we collect, use, and protect your information.">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-extrabold gradient-text tracking-tight mb-8">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <div class="glass-strong rounded-2xl p-6 sm:p-10 shadow-2xl space-y-6 text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed">

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-100 mb-3">Introduction</h2>
        <p>PepTalk Peptides ("we," "us," or "our") operates the website peptalkpeptides.com (the "Site"). This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you visit our Site. Please read this policy carefully. By using the Site, you consent to the practices described in this Privacy Policy.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-100 mb-3">Information We Collect</h2>

        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-2">Information You Provide</h3>
        <p>We may collect personal information that you voluntarily provide to us, including:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 mt-2 ml-2">
          <li><strong>Email address</strong> — when you subscribe to our newsletter or email list</li>
          <li><strong>Contact information</strong> — if you reach out to us via email or contact forms</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-2">Information Collected Automatically</h3>
        <p>When you visit the Site, certain information may be collected automatically, including:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 mt-2 ml-2">
          <li><strong>Device information</strong> — browser type, operating system, device type</li>
          <li><strong>Usage data</strong> — pages viewed, time spent on pages, referring URLs</li>
          <li><strong>IP address</strong> — used for analytics and security purposes</li>
          <li><strong>Cookies and similar technologies</strong> — see the Cookies section below</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-2">Information Stored Locally</h3>
        <p>Our calculator tool stores user preferences and settings in your browser's local storage (localStorage). This data remains on your device and is not transmitted to our servers. You can clear this data at any time through your browser settings.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-100 mb-3">How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use the information we collect for the following purposes:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 mt-2 ml-2">
          <li>To send you newsletters, updates, and educational content (if you subscribed)</li>
          <li>To improve and optimize the Site and our tools</li>
          <li>To analyze usage patterns and understand how visitors interact with the Site</li>
          <li>To respond to your inquiries and provide support</li>
          <li>To detect, prevent, and address technical issues or security threats</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-100 mb-3">Email Communications</h2>
        <p>If you subscribe to our email list, we will send you periodic emails related to peptide research, site updates, and educational content. You may opt out of these communications at any time by clicking the "unsubscribe" link at the bottom of any email or by contacting us directly. We will not sell, rent, or share your email address with third parties for their marketing purposes.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-100 mb-3">Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
        <p>We may use cookies, web beacons, and similar tracking technologies to collect information about your browsing activity on the Site. Cookies are small data files stored on your device that help us improve your experience and understand site usage.</p>
        <p class="mt-2">Types of cookies we may use:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 mt-2 ml-2">
          <li><strong>Essential cookies</strong> — necessary for the Site to function properly</li>
          <li><strong>Analytics cookies</strong> — help us understand how visitors use the Site</li>
          <li><strong>Preference cookies</strong> — remember your settings and preferences</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-2">You can control cookies through your browser settings. Disabling cookies may affect the functionality of certain features on the Site.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-100 mb-3">Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>We may use third-party services that collect, monitor, and analyze information to improve our Site. These may include:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 mt-2 ml-2">
          <li><strong>Google Analytics</strong> — for website usage analytics</li>
          <li><strong>Google Sheets / Google Apps Script</strong> — for processing email subscriptions</li>
          <li><strong>GitHub Pages</strong> — for website hosting</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-2">These third-party services have their own privacy policies addressing how they use your information. We encourage you to review their policies.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-100 mb-3">Affiliate Links</h2>
        <p>The Site contains affiliate links to third-party websites (such as Peptide Restore). When you click on these links, the third-party website may collect information about you in accordance with their own privacy policies. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of third-party websites.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-100 mb-3">Data Security</h2>
        <p>We implement reasonable administrative, technical, and physical security measures to protect your personal information. However, no method of transmission over the Internet or electronic storage is 100% secure. While we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect your personal information, we cannot guarantee its absolute security.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-100 mb-3">Data Retention</h2>
        <p>We retain your personal information only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes for which it was collected, including to satisfy any legal, accounting, or reporting requirements. Email addresses will be retained until you unsubscribe or request deletion.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-100 mb-3">Your Rights</h2>
        <p>Depending on your location, you may have certain rights regarding your personal information, including:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 mt-2 ml-2">
          <li>The right to access the personal information we hold about you</li>
          <li>The right to request correction of inaccurate personal information</li>
          <li>The right to request deletion of your personal information</li>
          <li>The right to opt out of email communications</li>
          <li>The right to withdraw consent at any time</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-2">To exercise any of these rights, please contact us using the information provided below.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-100 mb-3">Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>The Site is not directed to individuals under the age of 18. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If we become aware that we have collected personal information from a child without parental consent, we will take steps to delete that information.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-100 mb-3">Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated "Last updated" date. Your continued use of the Site after any changes constitutes your acceptance of the revised Privacy Policy.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-100 mb-3">Contact Us</h2>
        <p>If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or wish to exercise your data rights, please contact us at:</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-gray-200">PepTalk Peptides<br/>Email: privacy@peptalkpeptides.com</p>
      </section>

      <p class="text-gray-500 text-xs pt-4 border-t border-white/10">Last updated: February 2026</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
